SAMA and MAMA-nominated duo MFR Souls is set to drop a third project titled T-Squared EP today following the success of their album Healers of The Soul with lead single and club banger Uthando featuring Aymos. MFR Souls, from Katlehong on the east of Johannesburg, was formed in 2013, four years after the duo first met in 2009. The platinum-selling duo introduced a new sensational sound in the house genre commonly known as amapiano. They are known for the success of their platinum-certified commercial hit Love You Tonight with DJ Maphorisa, Kabza de Small, Sha Sha. The hit surpassed a million views on their music video on YouTube. T-Squared is the name of the EP, referring to both Maero and Force Reloaded. Leading this body of work is a single Forever with Mandy ZA, platinum-selling artist Manu Worldstar, and Bozza from the legendary hip-hop group Skwatta Kamp. For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.